Christelle Colman is managing director and founder at Elite Risk Acceptances, an innovative high-net-worth insurance start-up which launched to the South African short-term insurance market in August 2018. Elite is a wholly-owned subsidiary of Old Mutual Insure and provides bespoke short-term insurance and personal risk management solutions to high-net worth individuals. Colman is also company spokesperson for Old Mutual Insure and has served as head: personal lines underwriting and product development within the group. Prior to Elite, Colman also held the position of CEO of Europ Assistance South Africa for two years, providing exposure and insight into the global insurance market. She is a member of the Institute of Directors. On this episode of Business Talk – Presented by EY – Colman shares some of the behavioural changes from clients in the wake of the Covid pandemic, while talking through some of the biggest mistakes policy holders are making around claims. Colman also discusses the the rollout of the Adjudication of Road Traffic Offences (Aarto) Act and its impact on the insurance industry. The full interview is embedded below. You can find all the Business Talk with Michael Avery interviews here. <span style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" data-mce-type="bookmark" class="mce_SELRES_start">﻿</span>